text: William Napper (1816–1897) was an English cricketer. William Napper or Naper may also refer to: * William Naper (died 1683), Fellow of the Royal Society * William Napper (MP for Trim) (1661–1708), Irish politician * William Napper (MP for Athboy) (c. 1716–after 1760), Irish politician * William Napper (Irish cricketer) (1880–1967) ==See also== * William Napier (disambiguation)
title: William Napper (disambiguation)
